 8 module Icalendar
 9   # A Journal calendar component is a grouping of
10   # component properties that represent one or more descriptive text
11   # notes associated with a particular calendar date. The "DTSTART"
12   # property is used to specify the calendar date that the journal entry
13   # is associated with. Generally, it will have a DATE value data type,
14   # but it can also be used to specify a DATE-TIME value data type.
15   # Examples of a journal entry include a daily record of a legislative
16   # body or a journal entry of individual telephone contacts for the day
17   # or an ordered list of accomplishments for the day. The Journal
18   # calendar component can also be used to associate a document with a
19   # calendar date.
20   class Journal < Component

32     ical_property :summary
